<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2>Alliance Service</h2>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p>
            Pulling data from the alliance level will always include the alliance data at the highest level of the returned data. 
            It will not allow you to specify which guild or player you want to focus on. 
            To do that, please use the <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Guild", new { Area = "Api" })">guild service</a> or the 
            <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Player", new { Area = "Api" })">player service</a> respectively.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="well col-md-12">
        <h4>Base URL</h4>
        <p>
            The base URL for all alliance related queries is:
            <blockquote>
                <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Alliance", new { Area = "Api", id = 1 })">http://www.swgohboards.com/api/alliance/1</a>
            </blockquote>
            ...which will also return the basic information of our alliance.
        </p>
        <br/>
        <h4>Guilds</h4>
        <p>
            If you want to view data for <strong>all guilds</strong> in the alliance, use the following URL:
            <blockquote>
                <a href="@Url.Action("Guilds", "Alliance", new { Area = "Api", id = 1 })">http://www.swgohboards.com/api/alliance/1/guilds</a>
            </blockquote>
            The "GuildId"s returned from this query can be used in the <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Guild", new { Area = "Api" })">guild service</a> 
            to get data specifc to one of the member guilds.
        </p>
        <br/>
        <h4>Players</h4>
        <p>
            If you want to view data for <strong>all players</strong> in the alliance, use the following URL:
            <blockquote>
                <a href="@Url.Action("Players", "Alliance", new { Area = "Api", id = 1 })">http://www.swgohboards.com/api/alliance/1/players</a>
            </blockquote>
            The "PlayerId"s returned from this query can be used in the <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Player", new { Area = "Api" })">player service</a>
            to get data specifc to one specific player.
        </p>
        <br/>
        <h4>Collections</h4>
        <p>
            If you want to view data for <strong>all characters</strong> in the alliance, use the following URL:
            <blockquote>
                <a href="@Url.Action("Collections", "Alliance", new { Area = "Api", id = 1 })">http://www.swgohboards.com/api/alliance/1/collections</a>
            </blockquote>
            Note: This query may take some time to run due to the amount of data being returned.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>